{
    "id": "sysadmin/resource-monitoring",
    "title": "Monitor System Resources",
    "description": "Track CPU, memory, and disk on your Ubuntu laptop, then level up by observing a remote colony node.",
    "image": "/assets/quests/linux_resource_monitoring_dashboard.jpg",
    "npc": "/assets/npc/orion.jpg",
    "start": "start",
    "dialogue": [
        {
            "id": "start",
            "text": "Monitoring starts local. Your Ubuntu laptop is enough to learn `top`, `free`, and `df` before you coordinate multiple machines.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "multi-node-brief",
                    "text": "Why involve a Raspberry Pi node at all?"
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "operations",
                    "text": "Let's capture resource snapshots"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "multi-node-brief",
            "text": "Metaguild runs remote colony infrastructure on dedicated nodes. Your laptop is the dev cockpit; the Pi node is the live colony device. This quest teaches both single-node basics and next-level multi-node observability.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "operations",
                    "text": "Got it\u2014teach me both levels"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "operations",
            "text": "Capture one baseline from your laptop, then one from the remote colony node. Save command outputs with timestamps so incidents can be traced later.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "process",
                    "process": "sysadmin-capture-local-resource-snapshot",
                    "text": "Run top/free/df on Ubuntu laptop and save resource-snapshot.txt"
                },
                {
                    "type": "process",
                    "process": "sysadmin-capture-colony-node-resource-snapshot",
                    "text": "Collect top/df output from remote colony node"
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "quiz-1",
                    "text": "Both snapshots ready\u2014start monitoring quiz",
                    "requiresItems": [
                        {
                            "id": "6d49ab13-1a76-4022-a4ad-fafed2f30687",
                            "count": 1
                        },
                        {
                            "id": "0a7796cd-f5ff-4e48-9403-2cdf03b0cbed",
                            "count": 1
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "quiz-1",
            "text": "Quiz 1/5: In `top`, what usually indicates CPU saturation?",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "quiz-2",
                    "text": "High `%us`/`%sy` and consistently high load averages"
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "retry-quiz",
                    "text": "A large amount of free disk space"
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "retry-quiz",
                    "text": "The hostname ends with .local"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "quiz-2",
            "text": "Quiz 2/5: Which command gives a quick, human-readable filesystem usage summary?",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "quiz-3",
                    "text": "df -h"
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "retry-quiz",
                    "text": "du -a /"
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "retry-quiz",
                    "text": "free -m"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "quiz-3",
            "text": "Quiz 3/5: Which command shows memory totals in mebibytes?",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "quiz-4",
                    "text": "free -m"
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "retry-quiz",
                    "text": "pwd -m"
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "retry-quiz",
                    "text": "lsmem --disk"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "quiz-4",
            "text": "Quiz 4/5: Why capture snapshots with timestamps during investigations?",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "quiz-5",
                    "text": "To compare behavior over time and correlate with incidents"
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "retry-quiz",
                    "text": "To reduce RAM usage by itself"
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "retry-quiz",
                    "text": "Because `top` requires UTC for output"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "quiz-5",
            "text": "Quiz 5/5: What's the key value of monitoring both laptop and colony node?",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "finish",
                    "text": "You can separate local dev issues from remote production-node problems"
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "retry-quiz",
                    "text": "It doubles CPU speed on both devices"
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "retry-quiz",
                    "text": "It disables the need for logs"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "retry-quiz",
            "text": "Not quite. Re-check your snapshots, then retry the monitoring quiz.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "operations",
                    "text": "Retry from operations"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "finish",
            "text": "Great monitoring discipline. You can observe a single Ubuntu machine and scale your instincts to a remote colony node.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "finish",
                    "text": "Claim monitoring rewards",
                    "requiresItems": [
                        {
                            "id": "6d49ab13-1a76-4022-a4ad-fafed2f30687",
                            "count": 1
                        },
                        {
                            "id": "0a7796cd-f5ff-4e48-9403-2cdf03b0cbed",
                            "count": 1
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        }
    ],
    "rewards": [
